    <title>Taylor Swift endorses Kamala Harris in response to fake AI Trump endorsement</title>
    <content type="html">  

    &lt;figure&gt;
      &lt;img alt="Taylor Swift | The Eras Tour - Zürich, Switzerland" src="https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/I2LEZTC9Jr7CVNCRh749yY_A9wM=/0x0:7308x4872/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73577949/2161375048.0.jpg" /&gt;
        &lt;figcaption&gt;Photo by Noam Galai/TAS24/Getty Images for TAS Rights Management&lt;/figcaption&gt;
    &lt;/figure&gt;

  &lt;p id="tkZpvV"&gt;Taylor Swift said on Tuesday that she plans to vote for Vice President Kamala Harris in November’s presidential election — and that AI-generated images circulating of herself pushed her in part to make her support public.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p id="sdiQRM"&gt;“Recently I was made aware that AI of ‘me’ falsely endorsing Donald Trump’s presidential run was posted to his site. It really conjured up my fears around AI, and the dangers of spreading misinformation,” Swift &lt;a href="https://www.instagram.com/p/C_wtAOKOW1z/"&gt;wrote in an Instagram post&lt;/a&gt;. “It brought me to the conclusion that I need to be very transparent about my actual plans for this election as a voter. The simplest way to combat misinformation is with the truth.”&lt;/p&gt;
